# Templates: HTML and Jinja Guidelines

## HTML Structure and Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements (<section>, <article>, <nav>) not generic <div>
- All form inputs need contextual aria-labels
- Ensure responsive design with appropriate viewport meta tags
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)

## Base Template
- Templates/base.html can be modified to add new blocks or parameters but existing structure and blocks must be preserved
- When modifying base.html, ensure backward compatibility with existing templates

## Jinja Best Practices
- Use `{% extends "base.html" %}`; macros for repeated widgets
- Prefer template inheritance over includes
- Macros for repeated form fields and buttons
- Use whitespace suppression `{%-` â€¦ `-%}` to avoid extra spaces
- Escape variables by default (`{{ var|e }}`)
- Avoid using the `|safe` filter unless absolutely necessary

## Template Organization
- Organize templates by feature or blueprint
- Keep reusable components in a shared directory
- Use consistent naming conventions